Hitachi to Build Trains in New $114 Million U.K. Plant, FT Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-05-26T01:27:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-26/hitachi-to-build-trains-in-new-114-million-u-k-plant-ft-says.html
Hitachi Rail  Europe , a subsidiary of
 Hitachi Ltd. (6501) , will today announce plans for a 70 million-pound
($114.2 million) train factory to be set up in Newton Aycliffe,
north-east England, the Financial Times reported, without
attribution.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 